 of Being Earnest (1951), but his versatility is demonstrated in a number of modest genre films including The Woman in Question (1950), The Young Lovers (1954) and Orders to Kill (1958).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh  aAlfred Hitchcock.  aAnthony Asquith.  aBritish cinema.  aFrench Without Tears.  aPygmalion.  aTerence Rattigan.  aWoman in Question.  adirector.  afilm makers.  asilent films.1 aRyall, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779434540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847794345423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847794345/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles